 Germany’s Federal Criminal Police Office (BKA) is to set up a unit to investigate hate crimes, according to a government plan seen by dpa on Wednesday. The move cames after a right-wing extremist attacked a synagogue in Halle in eastern Germany, killing two people near the building. As part of the nine-point plan, online platforms will be obliged to inform the BKA unit of content containing death threats or incitement to violence. Continue reading German police to set up hate crime unit after synagogue plot at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Akwa Ibom State government has rejected the plans by the state command of the Nigeria Police Force to set up an Anti-Terrorism Unit in the state. It added that judging from all indices that preceded the creation of such sensitive anti-crime unit, doing same in Akwa Ibom, which is at… December 27, 2018 In "News" People gather to protest the arrival of US President Donald Trump as he visits the Tree of Life synagogue on October 30, 2018 in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. File: Times United States President Donald Trump arrived in Pittsburgh as funerals began for the victims of last weekend’s anti-Semitic shooting at a synagogue… October 31, 2018 In "News" The Akwa Ibom State Government has rejected plans by the Nigeria Police to set up an anti-terrorism unit in the state. Continue reading Akwa Ibom govt rejects Police anti-terrorism unit at Vanguard News Nigeria. Akwa Ibom govt rejects Police anti-terrorism unit December 27, 2018 In "News"